<DIV style="position:absolute;top:933;left:458"><nobr><span class="ft7"><b>24</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:158;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">Inside this ‘black box’ is a client-server pair that handles all the<br>network operations, passing function references and parameters<br>one way and return values the other:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:527;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft19"><b>Figure 4: The Easysoft ODBC-ODBC Bridge</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:563;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft4"><b>Figure 5 on page 25</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:563;left:434"><nobr><span class="ft3">shows the system set up across a network.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:596;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">Comparing it with the model in</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:596;left:503"><nobr><span class="ft4"><b>Figure 3 on page 23</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:596;left:669"><nobr><span class="ft3">, the database is</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:620;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft6">replaced by a network connection on the client side and the OOB<br>Server replaces the ODBC application on the server side.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:677;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">From</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:677;left:308"><nobr><span class="ft4"><b>Figure 5 on page 25</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:677;left:481"><nobr><span class="ft3">you can see that:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:710;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:710;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft3">to the application the OOB Client is a standard ODBC driver</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:743;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:743;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft3">on the server the OOB Server is a standard ODBC application</span></nobr></DIV>
