<DIV style="position:absolute;top:36;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft10"><b>I N S T A L L A T I O N</b><br><i>Easysoft ODBC-ODBC Bridge</i></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:933;left:458"><nobr><span class="ft7"><b>30</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:368;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft19"><b>Figure 6: Client Server version compatability.</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:404;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">For example:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:437;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:437;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft3">Client version 1.1 will work with Server version 1.1, 1.2, 1.3 ...</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:470;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:470;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft3">Client version 1.1 might not work with Server version 2.0.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:503;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:503;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft3">Client version 1.4 might not work with Server version 1.3.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:598;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft6">Only the first two fields constitute the version number. The last digit<br>is known as ‘build number’ and does not affect compatibility.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:740;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">The name of the Easysoft ODBC-ODBC Bridge distribution file<br>varies from platform to platform, but is of the form:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:797;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:799;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft18">odbc-odbc-bridge-</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:799;left:471"><nobr><span class="ft18">x_y_z-platform.exe</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:797;left:671"><nobr><span class="ft3">(Windows)</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:830;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">– OR –</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:862;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:863;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft18">odbc-odbc-bridge-</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:863;left:471"><nobr><span class="ft18">x.y.z-platform.tar.gz</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:862;left:703"><nobr><span class="ft3">(Unix)</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:895;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">– OR –</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:203;left:405"><nobr><span class="ft19"><b>Server version</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:233;left:270"><nobr><span class="ft19"><b>Client version</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:233;left:451"><nobr><span class="ft20">n.m</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:233;left:577"><nobr><span class="ft20">n.m+1</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:233;left:712"><nobr><span class="ft20">n+1.m</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:263;left:316"><nobr><span class="ft20">n.m</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:263;left:458"><nobr><span class="ft20">Y</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:263;left:593"><nobr><span class="ft20">Y</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:263;left:728"><nobr><span class="ft20">N</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:293;left:307"><nobr><span class="ft20">n.m+1</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:293;left:458"><nobr><span class="ft20">N</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:293;left:593"><nobr><span class="ft20">Y</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:293;left:728"><nobr><span class="ft20">N</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:323;left:307"><nobr><span class="ft20">n+1.m</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:323;left:458"><nobr><span class="ft20">N</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:323;left:593"><nobr><span class="ft20">N</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:323;left:728"><nobr><span class="ft20">Y</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:545;left:279"><nobr><span class="ft11"><b>NB</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:536;left:340"><nobr><span class="ft5">Client version 1.0 will work with all Servers up to version<br>2.0 even though the table indicates otherwise.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:676;left:279"><nobr><span class="ft11"><b>NB</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:655;left:340"><nobr><span class="ft6">If you connect a Client and Server with mismatched<br>protocols, the Easysoft ODBC-ODBC Bridge will detect<br>and report this immediately.</span></nobr></DIV>
</DIV>
