<DIV style="position:absolute;top:374;left:525"><nobr><span class="ft3">).</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:422;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft17"><b>INSTALLATION</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:461;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft22"><b>Unpacking the distribution</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:488;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">The OOB distribution for UNIX platforms except MAC OS X and<br>QNX is distributed as a tar file. There are multiple copies of the<br>same distribution with different levels of compression. You unpack<br>the distribution as follows.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:593;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">If the distribution file has been gzipped (i.e. the filename ends in</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:619;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft18">.gz</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:617;left:293"><nobr><span class="ft3">), then use:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:652;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft18">gunzip odbc-odbc-bridge-</span></nobr></DIV>
