<DIV style="position:absolute;top:395;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">directory or the</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:396;left:386"><nobr><span class="ft18">&lt;unixODBCInstallDir&gt;/bin</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:395;left:637"><nobr><span class="ft3">directory.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:428;left:232"><nobr><span class="ft3">2. Type:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:463;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft18">./isql -v data_source_name</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:494;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft6">For example, to connect to the PostgreSQL data source illustrated<br>earlier in this section, you would type:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:553;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft18">./isql -v main</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:802;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">If your server DBMS requires authentication, you should include the<br>DBMS user name and password arguments in the</span></nobr></DIV>
