<DIV style="position:absolute;top:553;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">If the wrong port is specified or some other service is listening on the<br>specified OOB Server port, then you will get a variety of errors, such<br>as when pointing</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:602;left:401"><nobr><span class="ft18">oobping</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:601;left:481"><nobr><span class="ft3">at an SMTP server on port</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:602;left:697"><nobr><span class="ft18">25</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:601;left:719"><nobr><span class="ft3">:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:635;left:304"><nobr><span class="ft18">oobping -h myserver -t 25</span></nobr></DIV>
