<DIV style="position:absolute;top:59;left:602"><nobr><span class="ft9"><i>Easysoft ODBC-ODBC Bridge</i></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:158;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">[6] attempts to connect to each data source in the local</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:160;left:701"><nobr><span class="ft18">odbc.ini</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:182;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">file. Whether the connection fails or succeeds is displayed in a<br>Status column. If the connection fails, diagnostics are provided.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:325;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">[7] builds up a connection string for the OOB Client ODBC driver but<br>with values you specify to the demo program. You are prompted for<br>each value in turn (the default values build up a connection string to<br>the demo data source on</span></nobr></DIV>
