<DIV style="position:absolute;top:371;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft6">iodbctest is a command line ODBC application that is supplied with<br>iODBC. Use it to test your OOB data sources. If a connection can<br>successfully be made, you can query the remote database by<br>executing SQL statements in iodbctest.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:476;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft17"><b>To test an OOB Client data source</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:509;left:232"><nobr><span class="ft3">1. Open Terminal in the</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:511;left:432"><nobr><span class="ft18">/Applications/Utilities</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:509;left:685"><nobr><span class="ft3">folder.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:542;left:232"><nobr><span class="ft3">2. At the shell prompt, type:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:577;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft18">iodbctest</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:608;left:232"><nobr><span class="ft3">3. Type DSN=</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:610;left:353"><nobr><span class="ft18">name</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:641;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">where</span></nobr></DIV>
