<DIV style="position:absolute;top:215;left:360"><nobr><span class="ft20">0x8000</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:215;left:434"><nobr><span class="ft33">If AllowDSNBrowse is not enabled then OOB Clients<br>cannot obtain a list of SYSTEM DSNs from the OOB<br>Server. This affects the ODBC API function</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:269;left:434"><nobr><span class="ft18">SQLBrowseConnect()</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:269;left:633"><nobr><span class="ft20">and the population of</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:287;left:434"><nobr><span class="ft33">the TargetDSN dropdown in the OOB Client Setup<br>dialogue. The default is on.</span></nobr></DIV>
