<DIV style="position:absolute;top:36;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft10"><b>REPORTING AND STATISTICS</b><br><i>Easysoft ODBC-ODBC Bridge</i></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:933;left:455"><nobr><span class="ft7"><b>266</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:158;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft6">Change the 60 (the refresh time in seconds) to your preferred<br>setting.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:385;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft17"><b>DSN STATISTICS</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:415;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft6">The Easysoft ODBC-ODBC Bridge records each DSN to which it is<br>connected and displays a table of DSN statistics:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:679;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft19"><b>Figure 68: DSN data on the Web Administrator Statistics screen</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:715;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">The information shown in the table per DSN is:</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:748;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:748;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft21"><b>Number of connections to this DSN - </b>By comparing this<br>number for each DSN you can see which is the busiest data<br>source on your server.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:829;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">•</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:829;left:288"><nobr><span class="ft21"><b>Total time connected to this DSN - </b>This is concurrent time so<br>two concurrent connections, connected for the same 5 seconds<br>registers as 10 seconds total time.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:272;left:279"><nobr><span class="ft11"><b>NB</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:215;left:340"><nobr><span class="ft6">Note that setting the refresh time to a very low value will<br>increase the workload on the OOB Server process which<br>handles HTTP requests. As this may reduce the response<br>time to the Easysoft ODBC-ODBC Bridge ODBC server<br>thread, times much less than 60 seconds are not<br>recommended.</span></nobr></DIV>
</DIV>
