<DIV style="position:absolute;top:395;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">page into links to further pages, allowing you to browse down<br>through the data source and its tables, columns and data.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:452;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">You may be prompted for a database user name and password<br>when first clicking on a DSN.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:509;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft5">The OOB Server attempts an initial connection without the ODBC<br>UID/PWD attributes, but if that fails with an authentication error<br>(</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:559;left:267"><nobr><span class="ft18">28000</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:557;left:321"><nobr><span class="ft3">) an authentication challenge will be issued, where the realm</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:581;left:261"><nobr><span class="ft3">is the name of the DSN.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:618;left:279"><nobr><span class="ft11"><b>NB</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:614;left:340"><nobr><span class="ft3">DSNs cannot be browsed using trusted connections.</span></nobr></DIV>
</DIV>
